TITLE: "Israeli defense minister calls on Netanyahu to halt overhaul of courts"
AUTHOR: Steve Hendrix
DESCRIPTION: Israel’s defense minister, a senior ally of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, called for a freeze on the government’s attempt to remake the judicial system.

TITLE: "Putin says Russia will station tactical nukes in Belarus"
DESCRIPTION: Russian President Vladimir Putin announced plans on Saturday to station tactical nuclear weapons in neighboring Belarus.

TITLE: "2 dead, 5 missing in chocolate factory explosion"
DESCRIPTION: An explosion at a chocolate factory in Pennsylvania on Friday killed five people and left six people missing, authorities said.

TITLE: "Rule of law on the ballot in Wisconsin Supreme Court justice runoff election"
AUTHOR: Michael McKenna
DESCRIPTION: The most interesting and perhaps most important single political campaign in 2023 is occurring right now over the seventh and decisive seat on the Wisconsin Supreme Court.

TITLE: "Corrupting our children is one of the left's favorite tactics"
AUTHOR: Don Feder
DESCRIPTION: The enemies of civilization, the army of the "woke," are sadists -- period.

TITLE: "Islamic holy month of Ramadan celebrated around the world"
AUTHOR: USA TODAY
DESCRIPTION: Ramadan is designed for fasting, time with loved ones and prayer, including asking for forgiveness for sins. Muslims believe it was during this month God gave the Qur'an to Prophet Muhammad and told him he was in charge of carrying God's message.

TITLE: "‘What can we do?’: Millions in African countries need power"
AUTHOR: Mogomotsi Magome
DESCRIPTION: From Zimbabwe, where many must work at night because it’s the only time there is power, to Nigeria where collapses of the grid are frequent, the reliable supply of electricity remains elusive across Africa.

TITLE: "Greene’s DC jail visit pulls GOP closer to Jan. 6 rioters"
AUTHOR: Lisa Mascaro
DESCRIPTION: Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene swept into the District of Columbia jail to check on conditions for the Jan. 6 defendants, with Republican lawmakers handshaking and high-fiving the prisoners, who chanted “Let’s Go Brandon!” — a coded vulgarity against President Joe Biden — as the group left.

TITLE: "Trump rallying supporters in Waco ahead of possible charges"
DESCRIPTION: Staring down a possible indictment, a defiant Donald Trump is hoping to put on a show of force Saturday as he holds the first rally of his 2024 presidential campaign in a city made famous by deadly resistance against law enforcement.

TITLE: "Texas police: Migrants found ‘suffocating’ in train; 2 dead"
DESCRIPTION: Two migrants were found dead and at least 10 were hospitalized Friday after police in South Texas received a call that they were “suffocating” in a freight train traveling near the U.S.-Mexico border.
